<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
  <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Section 16: KiP Edition</h2>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">What is KiP?</h3>
  <p class="mb-4 text-white/70">
    <strong>KiP - Knowledge is Power</strong> is a planned self-hosted edition of Meridian Console for
    organizations that want to run the entire platform on their own infrastructure.
  </p>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Target Use Cases</h3>
  <div class="scope-panel mb-6">
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-white/70">
      <li>- Enterprise/corporate game server management</li>
      <li>- LAN events and tournaments</li>
      <li>- Educational institutions</li>
      <li>- Privacy-conscious organizations</li>
      <li>- Air-gapped environments</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Differences from SaaS</h3>
  <table class="scope-table mb-6">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>SaaS</th>
        <th>KiP</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Hosting</td><td>Meridian-managed</td><td>Self-hosted</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Billing Service</td><td>Included</td><td>Excluded</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Updates</td><td>Automatic</td><td>Manual/scheduled</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Support</td><td>Included</td><td>Separate agreement</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-400">Timeline</h3>
  <div class="scope-callout">
    <strong>Post-MVP:</strong> KiP development begins after SaaS MVP reaches stable state. Architecture
    is designed from day one to support this deployment model.
  </div>
</div>
